Garba Pwul (SAN) has said that the judiciary has flourished better under President Muhammadu Buhari than in  previous administrations. Pwul, who spoke yesterday in Jos, the Plateau State capital, while interacting with newsmen, said the current administration has tremendous respect for the judiciary. He said the administration is  always willing to abide by its decisions. He commended President Buhari for giving courts free hand to discharge their responsibilities. Buhari inaugurates Committee on Autonomy of State Legislature, Judiciary I will continue to reposition police, judiciary – Buhari ICMC wants financial autonomy for judiciary